<subSubSection id="C3136559FFE6FFE7FCECFB74E350FA78" pageId="35" pageNumber="442" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB636D2FFE6FFE7FCECFB74E350FA78" blockId="35.[806,1392,1148,1566]" pageId="35" pageNumber="442">
For decades this species was considered part of M. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D51FFE6FFE7FC09FB59E27BFAF2" authorityName="Clinton" authorityYear="1822" baseAuthorityName="Erxleben" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[962,1094,1262,1291]" class="Mammalia" family="Cervidae" genus="Mazama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="35" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="americana">americana</taxonomicName>
. The scientific name refers to an animal the explorer and naturalist F. Hernandez called “temamacame” in 1651. Three subspecies are recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
